text.__SUMMARY__: Dendrobium moniliforme, known as carrot fern in English, Shihu in Chinese and Sekkoku in Japanese, is a species of orchid. It is native to Japan, Korea, China, the Himalayas, and northern Indochina.In 17th century Japan, royalty used it to perfume clothing.
